10. Use Container Widget with alignment property in Flutter App Development

✅ Explanation (Exam-Oriented)

The Container widget in Flutter uses the alignment property to position its child inside the container.

It controls where the child widget appears
Uses predefined values like:
Alignment.center
Alignment.topLeft
Alignment.bottomRight

//main code

import 'package:flutter/material.dart';

void main() {
  runApp(MyApp());
}

class MyApp extends StatelessWidget {
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return MaterialApp(
      home: ContainerAlignmentExample(),
    );
  }
}

class ContainerAlignmentExample extends StatelessWidget {
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return Scaffold(
      appBar: AppBar(
        title: Text("Container Alignment Example"),
      ),
      body: Center(
        child: Container(
          height: 150,
          width: 250,
          color: Colors.teal,
          alignment: Alignment.bottomRight,
          child: Text(
            "Aligned Text",
            style: TextStyle(color: Colors.white, fontSize: 18),
          ),
        ),
      ),
    );
  }
}